cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DS

The paper discusses the security of public key validation protocols, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The proposal of a distributed transparent key infrastructure (DTKI) involves distributed systems (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE) aspects. The paper also discusses the reliance on trusted parties, which relates to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and the formalization of the public log data structure, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
